description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic RMN to join the Brighton and Hove CAMHS team, to work within the ADHD pathway. You will join an existing multi-disciplinary team providing a range of therapeutic interventions. We are looking for a newly qualified nurse, or a more experienced nurse interested in a career in CAMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your duties would include: providing evidence based assessment and treatment of children, young people, their families and carers; and to work as valued team member in support of the ADHD caseload, including the assessment, review and management of risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer excellent supervision, support, training and development opportunities including a band 5 preceptorship program and have strong links with the Universities of Sussex and Brighton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a Golden Hello, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;for more information contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sarah Goodfellow, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Nurse, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAMHS - Brighton and Hove&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
